SDLC Enterprise Framework
Version: 5.3.0
Archived: January 28, 2026
Superseded By: 6.0.0

Key Features (5.3.0):
- Stage Dependency Matrix (ADR-041)
- Stage Exit Criteria (per-tier documentation requirements)
- Sprint-Stage Integration (multi-stage sprint handling)
- Quality Assurance System (Section 7 - Anti-Vibecoding)
  - Vibecoding Index (0-100 composite score)
  - Progressive Routing (Green → Yellow → Orange → Red)
  - Auto-Generation Layer (Intent, Ownership, Context, Attestation)
  - Kill Switch Criteria
- Tier-Specific Stage Requirements (LITE/PRO/ENTERPRISE)
- Stage Transition Checklists

Reason for Major Upgrade:
- 6.0.0 introduces Unified Specification Standard (Section 8)
- Breaking change: YAML frontmatter required for all new specs
- Breaking change: BDD (GIVEN-WHEN-THEN) format required
- New: Lightweight Design Decisions (DD-NNNN)
- New: SPEC_DELTA.md version tracking
- New: Context Authority Methodology (Dynamic AGENTS.md)

Timeline:
- 5.3.0 Released: January 28, 2026 (AM)
- 5.3.0 Archived: January 28, 2026 (PM)
- 6.0.0 Released: January 28, 2026 (PM)
